  "why": "PVDF-HFP-SN-0.1LAWTP solid composite electrolyte shows the optimum ionic conductivities of 3.03×10^-5 S/cm at 30°C and 1×10^-4 S/cm at 50°C (Fig. 4a–b). Its electrochemical stability window (decomposition voltage) is 4.8 V (Fig. 4e). The Li-ion transference number tLi+ is 0.478 measured in Li/SCE/Li cells (Table 2). Li/PVDF-HFP-SN-0.1LAWTP/Li symmetric cells exhibit lower and stable polarization and operate for 1000 cycles at 0.1 mA/cm^2 without short circuit (Fig. 7). In full cells (LFP/PVDF-HFP-SN-0.1LAWTP/Li), at 0.5C and 50°C: initial 158.06 mAh/g, 133.82 mAh/g after 200 cycles (84.66% retention); at room temperature 0.5C: 142.69→136.41 mAh/g after 500 cycles (95.60% retention), CE >99% after the first cycle (Fig. 8–9). With 5 μL liquid electrolyte infiltration, ionic conductivity increases to 3.64×10^-4 S/cm (30°C) and 7×10^-4 S/cm (50°C), and stability window ~4.5 V (Fig. 5)."
}

